let me know what you think this is this is may th poem it's as bad as the others i think i use the word 'awful' to much this one is another depressing poem i know that you've all probably had your fill of poems like this but it is pathetically all i have at the moment let me know what you think untitled and all that you do is mock me with mimicry lay blame at my feet with a claim of moods finicky and though you re the one whom i yearn for the most you take joy and you laugh while my tender heart roasts and each day anew i expect naught but love from you and each day again i find this hope snatched away by you there s naught in my chest but a sad little hole a horrible pit used to torture my soul and it s there that you ve found a perch to your liking a place you can crush all i am by just striking and yet i love you now more than i did just this morning though for my lost soul i will always be mourning it's actually pretty good only tiny annoying thing i found was the rhyming of words like mourning and morning you and you it just sounds like you've run out of ideas but other than that it's good Shaggy dog story David Bowie Poetry Black Victor Hugo The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Ranma __ characters Hell Pitaten Teen Girl Squad Parsifal Squidward Tentacles Yehuda Halevi 2000 Australian Grand Prix Fitz Hugh Ludlow Adam Mickiewicz The Death Gate Cycle Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Conan the Barbarian Jon Secada Emily Dickinson Spike (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Das Lied von der Erde The Smashing Pumpkins Time Out of Mind Kain (Legacy of Kain) EastEnders Limerick (poetry) Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Dean Koontz Scenes from a Memory Ron and Fez Futurama (TV series - season 5) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Biblical poetry Little Britain Dead Like Me Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Yu-Gi-Oh! anime and manga characters Le Malade imaginaire The Yeomen of the Guard Whose Line Is It Anyway? Liam Gallagher Goodness and 